Description:
On-Trend Opulence with Flair and Flexibility
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Please also register your interest to attend the auction so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations and be contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior.
Simply stunning, this as-new architectural showpiece (c2019) is sure exceed all expectations thanks to its exceptional design, uncompromised quality, and absolute meticulous attention to detail - all in a convenient cul-de-sac with close proximity to the best of Keilor East. Beyond the bold facade, discover a lavish interior comprising three generous bedrooms (large master with fitted WIR) and study/home office (potential 4BR), together with a deluxe ensuite, equally-stylish main bathroom and separate powder rooms on each level - all with premium fittings and floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a lounge/retreat (upstairs) out to an undercover balcony with skyline views, spacious and versatile open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a gourmet kitchen with top-of-the-range Fisher & Paykel appliances and butler's pantry complete with second sink. Bathed in natural light, the home also boasts zoned ducted heating and refrigerated cooling, comprehensive security system (alarm, CCTV and video intercom), large laundry and excellent storage options, square-set ceilings, soft-close cabinetry and stone benchtops throughout. Completing the picture is an al-fresco entertaining deck and private back garden, plus internally-accessed garage (remote-control) and additional driveway parking. Walking distance to Centreway shops, cafes and Milleara Road buses, easy access to the Calder Freeway and a range of local schools including PEGS, Keilor Heights Primary School and Essendon Keilor College.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you.

IDEAL FIRST HOME / INVESTMENT OPPORTUNITY!
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSE MONDAY 29th JUNE @ 5.00PM
Perfectly located within quiet surrounds and on a desirable block measuring 541sqm (approx) this brick veneer home promises an exciting opportunity for renovators, families, market entrants and investors.
A warm and welcoming interior reveals three good sized bedrooms, central bathroom, formal lounge, spacious kitchen, family sized meals area & polished hardwood flooring and roller shutters.
Outside, an undercover alfresco zone and large backyard offers plenty of room for relaxing and entertaining and a wide side drive provides ample off-street car accommodation.
Perfectly located offering easy access to St Peters Primary School, Milleara Shopping Centre, Overland Reserve, parks and freeways to CBD.

Description:
Large Family Home With Timeless Appeal
Please register your interest to attend or bid in a Brad Teal auction. Registrations allow us to maintain compliance with the latest government directions. All auctions will be held onsite and online. Please register to bid here: https://portal.bidtracker.com.au/auctions/0f616c1e-5751-40d3-9424-be5a62949fd7/register-bidder/
Perfect for the growing family, this expansive five bedroom plus study, three bathroom character home sits on a sizeable garden block of approx. 595m2 in a family friendly neighbourhood. Charming interiors, featuring formal entry hall, elegant fireside lounge, large light filled retreat and spacious open plan family/dining areas, provide great floor plan flexibility. Whilst paved outdoor zones and leafy gardens offer a quiet space for alfresco dining and entertaining. Warmed by timber cabinets and polished floorboards, a central kitchen displays stainless steel cooking appliances, dishwasher and breakfast bar. Spread across two spacious levels are five comfortable bedrooms and three refreshed bathrooms, including ground floor master with ensuite and walk-in-robe. Enhancing appeal, the home has been reblocked, replumbed and rewired, and also offers separate studio with home office/teenager retreat potential, plus BIRS, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, 3KW solar electricity, alarm, under stair storage and tandem carport. Close to Westfield Shopping Centre, Essendon Fields, St Christopher's primary, PEGS, parklands, buses and freeways.

Private Negotiation By Pennisi
The Obvious
Substantial block of land of approximately 600 square meters best suited to buyers looking to build their dream home or for the astute developer primed to develop multiple units, subject to council approvals.
The Village
Convenient proximity to everything from schools to shops, parkland and buses. Easy access to major arterials including Ring Road, Calder & Tullamarine Freeway to CBD.
The Clincher
Located in a growing pocket of Keilor East, get creative and capitalise on the substantial land size
Pennisi Real Estate, wish you every success with your property hunt.
For more information on this property or to chat about one of the many other Private Negotiation properties we have available please call or email us today.
***PLEASE NOTE*** Due to the Coronavirus outbreak there will be no open homes scheduled for this property. In the best interests of our community, all inspections will be conducted as one-on-one private viewings until further notice.
To help with increased demand, our team is extending normal hours to be available anytime, including evenings and all weekend. To arrange a private viewing, please call our 24-Hour Buyer Hotline on 9379 5616 and advise us during this call if you have recently travelled. When your booking is confirmed, well greet you at the property with a smile instead of a handshake, then its business as usual!
Thank you for your understanding and cooperation during this time.

Description:
Family Flexibility with Corner Credentials!
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Please also register your interest to attend the auction so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations and be contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior.
Occupying one of the area's larger allotments (approx 671sqm) on the corner of Cudgewa Place, this attractive single-level home immediately provides a spacious and versatile family environment along with future options to further enhance, expand or possibly develop in the future (STCA). Flawlessly presented, the home's light-filled interior comprises three main bedrooms, together with a dedicated study/home office and two stylish bathrooms. Adding to its appeal is a formal dining room (or fourth bedroom), large front lounge, rear sunroom and separate kitchen/meals area complete with gas cooktop and Miele dishwasher. High ceilings throughout, the home also includes ducted heating and evaporative cooling for year-round comfort, laundry facilities and external roller shutters for added security. Step outside to discover a huge backyard with northerly aspect and paved entertaining area, plus a handy garden shed, large storeroom/workshop and lock-up garage via gated driveway. Walking distance to Centreway shops, cafes and Milleara Road buses, it also offers easy access to the Calder Freeway and a range of local schools including PEGS, Keilor Heights Primary School and Essendon Keilor College.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. Description:
Fantastic Suburban Opportunity
Beyond the beautiful, family friendly front yard, this proudly presented three bedroom brick residence sits on a block size of approx. 536m2. A spacious formal lounge opens to the delightful meals area, while the sundrenched kitchen is fully equipped with Fisher & Paykel stainless steel appliances, stone benchtops, glass splashback and ample glossy cabinetry. Crafted to entertain during every season, the grand alfresco flows to an expansive backyard surrounded by garden beds and access to a long driveway providing loads of OSP. Double sized carpeted bedrooms are fitted with mirrored BIRs for convenience and are serviced by the bright central bathroom featuring floating basin, large shower and separate toilet. Further luxuries include polished floorboards throughout, laundry with backyard access, zoned ducted heating plus split system air conditioning, alarm, garden shed, remote controlled gates and remote lockup garage with space for work station. Only 25 minutes from the CBD, its close to Green Gully Reserve, Watergardens Shopping Centre, transport, schools and the Calder Freeway/Western Ring Road.

Description:
Enhanced Family Favourite with Gorgeous Garden Surrounds
***This property is available for inspection by appointment-Please contact us to arrange a suitable time****
A delightful family environment that's ready to simply move in and enjoy, this attractive home is sure to make an impression with its flexible floorplan and quality features throughout - all on a wide landscaped allotment with exceptional urban convenience. Impeccably presented and bathed in natural light, the home's single-level design comprises three generous bedrooms (all with built-in robes) and versatile sunroom/home office, together with a modern bathroom with floor-to-ceiling tiles and separate WC. The spacious central lounge flows through to the open dining area complemented by a contemporary kitchen complete with tiled splashbacks, quality cooking appliances and Fisher & Paykel dishwasher. Other highlights of this inviting family home include ducted heating, evaporative cooling and additional split-system air conditioner, solid hardwood floors and a family-sized laundry. Double doors reveal an al-fresco style entertaining deck overlooking the expansive backyard with lush lawn area and established perimeter gardens, plus the added appeal of a deep single garage (remote-control) and adjoining workshop. Walking distance to Rosehill Park and Steele Creek trails, it's also close to public and private schools (including St Bernard's College and PEGS), Rachelle Road buses, as well as a choice of popular shopping precincts and easy freeway access.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending a Private Appointment, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from our team members, and if requested wait outside until the property is ready for the appointment. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.
